<div id="review_2088588764" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2088588764" />
    <a title="Ram Alsrougi" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/55615999-ram-alsrougi"><img alt="Ram Alsrougi" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1563277979p2/55615999.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2088588764?book_show_action=true">Dec 04, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ram Alsrougi" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ram Alsrougi" href="/user/show/55615999-ram-alsrougi">Ram Alsrougi</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780679410447" href="/book/show/970972.The_Prince">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2088588764" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6899831670498566774">&quot;Leader should be loved and feared at the same time... but since love and fear can hardly exist together, if we must choose between them, it is far safer to be feared than loved.&quot;<br/><br/>I&apos;ve always found it very difficult to rate classic works, because most of them are uneven. Definitely, this book is highly recommended If you&apos;ve watched Game of Thrones.<br/>The book contains Machiavelli&apos;s advice to the Italian ruler back then, it has shaped political thoughts for +500 years.<br/>I was really shocked by how grea</span>
  <span id="freeText6899831670498566774" style="display:none">"Leader should be loved and feared at the same time... but since love and fear can hardly exist together, if we must choose between them, it is far safer to be feared than loved."<br /><br />I've always found it very difficult to rate classic works, because most of them are uneven. Definitely, this book is highly recommended If you've watched Game of Thrones.<br />The book contains Machiavelli's advice to the Italian ruler back then, it has shaped political thoughts for +500 years.<br />I was really shocked by how great and frank this book is, because I have known very little about this book before opening it, and my knowledge about it was limited to the idea that Machiavelli was the intellectual twin of Vlad the Impaler!. 😂😅<br /><br />"If Moses, Cyrus, Theseus, and Romulus were unarmed, they would not have made others respect their constitutions for long periods."<br /><br />What seems to make this book so very accessible and serious is that Machiavelli uses history to prove his point and gives one or many examples for each of his recommendations, from "Prophet" Moses, Alexander, Darius, Cyrus, the rulers of the Roman and Greek Empire. 🔥<br />And more interestingly, when you read these advices, you even remember the rulers and kings who lived after the author himself until this day; this proves Machiavelli's statements several times more than the author's own lifetime. 👏<br /><br />Reading this book will help you to see how you look at politics and to be more open-ended, and to help your knowledge grow at the end. It is genius, foxy, practical, pragmatic and even more, it is foundational for those who want to gain and remain in power.<br />I think many people -especially Arabs- over-make Machiavelli unfairly as the symbol of evilness, and few works of literature have as well misunderstood him because of his politics. However, there are many of concepts that should stay in this book which they don’t belong to the democracy of today, and a few somewhat are relevant which you may apply to our time circumstances. 😅<br /><br />Well, I guess I'm off to conquer my own country now hehe!. 😁😂</span>
  <a data-text-id="6899831670498566774" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


